=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Guides_Tour_of_UGens_ex52 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_bright noisy sound, with noise oscillator character around 53 Hz, featuring very_slow attack and impulsive envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, energy distribution is late, filtered with steep_rolloff character, and spectrally rich.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: very_slow
  brightness: very_bright
  crest_factor_db: impulsive
  envelope_flatness: very_dynamic
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: noisy
  spectral_complexity_mean: rich
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: late

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 52.6681
  harmonic_decay_rate: 0.0621
  harmonic_regularity: 0.5902
  pitch_clarity: 0.9060
  inharmonicity: 0.0502
  type: noise
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -0.0188
  resonance_freq: 0.0000

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: Tour of UGens Example 52
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Guides/Tour_of_UGens.html
// Tags: Tour_of_UGens, Guides
// ---
// --- Example 52 ---
(
// Dust randomly triggers Decay to create an exponential
// decay envelope for the WhiteNoise input source
{
z = Decay.ar(Dust.ar(1,0.5), 0.3, WhiteNoise.ar);
DelayN.ar(z, 0.1, 0.1, 1, z); // input is mixed with delay via the add input
}.play
)
